RACE.RACE_TEXT: TURF PARADISE RACE 1 6 1/2F Dirt CR: 80. Claiming Purse 16400. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Weight, 121 lbs. Claiming Price $20,000. Arizona Bred Claiming Price $30,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: ECHO CANYON raced unhurried early, moved six-wide through the turn, responded when set down for the drive and surged late to be up in time. NASHVILLE SKYLINE set a pressured pace, opened a clear margin nearing the five-sixteenths pole but could not resist the winner late. BIG CREED was reserved just off the leaders early, moved three-wide through the turn, came out to bump PASSION OF JOE'S late and finished willingly. PASSION OF JOE'S pressed the pace while racing four-wide, was bumped by BIG CREED late and finished evenly. CONRADO settled off the leaders early, moved five-wide through the turn and weakened. FLASHIN ACES lost footing and steadied soon after the start, raced five-wide through the turn and did not offer a bid. THE STEWARDS CONDUCTED AN INQUIRY CONCERNING THE BUMPING BETWEEN BIG CREED AND PASSION OF JOE'S LATE AND AFTER REVIEWING THE FILMS MADE NO CHANGE. THE RACE WAS HAND TIMED.
